Game - Interface in edu.harvard.cs262.DistributedGame
Game is an interface that is implemented by every game so that it can interact with the client and server system.
GameClient - Interface in edu.harvard.cs262.GameClient
A GameClient is a general interface allowing a client to receive messages from the server indicating which other slave servers exist in the distributed system.

GameServer - Interface in edu.harvard.cs262.GameServer

GameSnapshot - Interface in edu.harvard.cs262.DistributedGame
The GameSnapshot interface represents the current snapshot of the game, which clients can render to display and view the current progression of the game.
GameState - Interface in edu.harvard.cs262.DistributedGame
The GameState interface represents the current state of the game, which is used by servers to execute commands on the game.
